      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm looking at some digitized census records from Henrico County, Virginia, around 1780. I've noticed some really weird swings in the population density between the 1770s and the 1790s that don't seem to align with the standard migration patterns for that period. What are some of the primary historical factors that might explain these kinds of sudden, significant fluctuations in colonial Virginia?",
