      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a fair point about the record-keeping being messy. But I'm looking at specific patches of land where the headcount goes from dozens to almost zero and then back up again within just a few years. It's so localized and sudden that it feels less like general \"bad record keeping\" and more like something specific happened in those exact spots. Is there any precedent in colonial history for localized \"disappearances\" or sudden shifts that aren't just migration or war?",
